On 5/11/05 12:37 PM, "Gervais, Pierre" <PGervais(-at-)BR.Kruger.com> wrote:

> I do not know when you say "casting of the fan" if
> you refer at the fan housing or at a part of the fan.

I mean the fan itself. The early baywindow fan had a cone shape near the
center and had a black plug installed there. The later fan had no plug and
an angled keyway. The vanagon fan has a more square keyway that allow you to
rotate the engine with a t-wrench using vw tool 3052.

